text: Tiu, also Teyew etc., was a ancient Egyptian Pharaoh who ruled in the Nile Delta.J. H. Breasted, History of Egypt from the Earliest Time to the Persian Conquest, 1909, p.36 He ruled in the Predynastic period in ancient Egyptian history. Tiu is mentioned in the Palermo Stone inscriptions, along with a small number of kings of Lower Egypt.J. H. Breasted, Ancient Records of Egypt, Part One, Chicago 1906, ยง90 Nothing else is known of his life or what he did while he was Pharaoh. == References == Category:Predynastic Pharaohs
title: Tiu (pharaoh)
